  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::HiddenCard
  cardID: balcony_card_02
  cardTitle: Threads of Tradition
  cardDescription: "The carpets and rugs you see here were not mere decoration\u2014they
    represented a family's wealth and a woman's skill. Berat was famous for its textile
    crafts, with patterns passed down through generations. Each geometric motif held
    meaning: diamonds symbolized protection, while birds represented freedom and
    messengers between worlds."
  detectionRadius: 3
  requiresDirectLook: 1
  interactionKey: 101
